Ansaldo, Fiat, Finmeccanica, Parmalat: Italian Equity Preview

-- B y   M a r c o   B e r t a c c h e
-- 
2011-03-02T07:40:03Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-01/ansaldo-fiat-finmeccanica-parmalat-italian-equity-preview.html
The following companies may be
active in Italian trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses and
share prices are from the previous close.  Italy’s benchmark  FTSE MIB Index  lost 239.34, or 1.1
percent, to 22,227.23 in Milan.  Ansaldo STS (STS IM): Finmeccanica SpA’s (FNC IM) railway
technology unit said 2010 net income rose to 95 million euros
($131 million). That beat the 91.5 million-euro average estimate
of nine analysts in a Bloomberg survey. The company proposed a
dividend of 28 euro cents and forecast revenue this year of as
much as 1.36 billion euros. The shares dropped 0.8 percent to
10.1 euros.    Fiat SpA  (F IM): Italian car registration fell 20.5 percent
in February to 160,329 units. Fiat brand car sales dropped 34
percent, while its Alfa Romeo brand gained 33 percent. The
shares fell 1.3 percent to 6.64 euros.    Finmeccanica SpA  (FNC IM): Italy’s biggest defense company
plans to report 2010 results. The shares rose 0.9 percent to
9.15 euros.    Mediaset SpA  (MS IM): Italy’s competition regulator said
that leaving to Prime Minister Silvio Berlusconi the decision to
extend a ban on acquisitions of newspapers by television
companies is “inappropriate.” Mediaset is the broadcast
company owned by Berlusconi.  The shares retreated 1.5 percent to 4.59 euros.    Parmalat SpA  (PLT IM): Groupe Lactalis may buy a 15 percent
stake in the dairy company held by Skagen AS, Mackenzie
Financial Corp. and Zenit Asset Management AB, Il Sole 24 Ore
reported, without saying how it obtained the information. The
stock gained 1.4 percent to 2.25 euros.  -- With assistance from Julie Cruz in  Frankfurt . Editors:
